---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Language" description="Learn the language of Vaelinya in small, clear steps.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Language</p>
    <h1>Learn the language of Vaelinya.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Start with a few living words. The language of Vaelinya should feel like discovery, not homework.</p>
    <p>Use this section when you want to understand names, meanings, sounds, and the small word-families that run underneath the stories.</p>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-language">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>Va</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">First route</p>
        <h2>Open the public lexicon</h2>
        <p>The lexicon gives each public word slowly: word, pronunciation, IPA, plain meaning, story use, and example sentence.</p>
        <a class="visual-callout-link" href="/language/lexicon/">Open the lexicon</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list" aria-label="Language routes">
      <a href="/language/lexicon/">Lexicon</a>
      <a href="/language/lexicon/home-shelter-recovery/">Word family: home, shelter, and recovery</a>
      <a href="/language/lexicon/belonging-recognition-personhood/">Word family: belonging, recognition, and personhood</a>
      <a href="/read/lina/">Words inside Lina’s stories</a>
    </div>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Coming next</p>
      <h2>Reference pages will come after the words are stable</h2>
      <p>These pages are planned, but they should not outrun the public lexicon.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Pronunciation</strong> — coming soon.</li>
        <li><strong>Grammar</strong> — coming soon.</li>
        <li><strong>Writing system</strong> — coming soon.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
